<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#00ff00">Originally posted by Freddo Frog on 12-12-2001 09:52 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">None of you really know me, I'm the lurkiest of lurkers but I have been following SEQ for a long time.

In fact, I've been using SEQ since the days before encryption was introduced to EQ. I've been using SEQ for such a long time that without it I doubt I would have persevered with EQ.

No, not because I could p h @ t  p h a r m or get ub3r loot but mainly just to get around, or more importantly to recover my corpse after an LD. 

Until my area got ADSL I was a modem user on an ISP that would random disconnect. The number of times you would die to a LD in some far off remote place you have no idea how you got to (because your char went off in NPC mode after being attacked) are too many to list and would have been acct stopping nightmares for me without SEQ.

SEQ offered other advantages obviously but me for me it helped equalise the bullshit that Verant made us endure.

Imagine my surpise then to discover that the CVS had been nerfed by one of the main SEQ developing contributers because of a new expansion release.

The deliberate SEQ NERF was also extremely lame. Protect us from ourselves bullshit I guess was the reasoning but maybe if Verant were seriously challenged by the Show EQ community they might just have to give in and enhance the game in the customers favour. 

Perhaps a SEQ radar type map for tracking classes, easier corpse recovery, less insane cruelty to players simply trying to navigate around or trying to get a bind etc. etc.

Of course the SEQ community won't know if they were really able to make a positive change to EQ and bop the $ hungry Sony in the nose. They won't know because they were too busy pandering to the evil one.

The only solution Verant should be able to take to stop SEQ and it's derivatives is to release the same tools in game and thus neuter the use of SEQ.

Thats just my .02c on it.

And please remember, it's not a crime to have an opinion.

Freddo Frog

P.s. For those who might not know yet, there is another product called SINS which means (SINS is not showeq) - people interested should search sourceforge on it.

P.p.s My SEQ and SINS are both working as best as can be expected, grey on zone in, decryted after pop. So I'm not looking for help, it was just my take on the CVS nerf.

[This message has been edited by Freddo Frog (edited 12-12-2001).]</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
